SIMPLE: spousal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spousal
<hw>Spous"al</hw> <pr>(-⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Espousal</er>, <er>Sponsal</er>, and <er>Spouse</er>.]</ety> <def>Of
or pertaining to a spouse or marriage; nuptial; matrimonial; conjugal;
connubial; bridal; <as>as, <ex>spousal</ex> rites; <ex>spousal</ex>
ornaments</as>.</def> <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spousal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spousal
<hw>Spous"al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Espousal</er>,
<er>Spouse</er>.]</ety> <def>Marriage; nuptials; espousal; -- generally
used in the plural; <as>as, the <ex>spousals</ex> of
Hippolita</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Boweth your head under that blissful yoke . . .⟦br⟧
Which that men clepeth <qex>spousal</qex> or wedlock.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spousals</qex> of the newborn year.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spouse</ent>⟦br⟧
